latestPosts.caption:
Prime Minister Narendra Modi has shown significant recognition and appreciation for the sport of Wushu, particularly concerning the achievements of Indian Wushu athletes.

Total International Achievements of Wushu in India:

* World Wushu Championships: India has won a total of 3 gold, 9 silver, and 16 bronze medals.

* Asian Games: India's medal tally at the Asian Games in Wushu stands at 2 silver and 8 bronze medals.

* India's Madel tally at the World Junior Wushu Championships: India has secured more then 20 medals.

* Sanda World Cup: India has won at least 1 gold and 6 silver medals across different editions. In the 10th Sanda World Cup (April 2025), India won 1 gold and 5 silver medals.

Other Notable International Tournament Achievements: more than 100 medals

* Wushu Sanda Athlete of the Year Award: Roshibina Devi Naorem was awarded this prestigious title by the International Wushu Federation in January 2024.

*Till now 6 Arjuna Awards have been received in Wushu.

#modi #india #wushu #sportstationsale

Honorable Kuldeep Handoo is indeed a remarkable figure in the world of Wushu. As India's first and only Dronacharya Awardee in Wushu, his influence on the sport has been profound. Under his expert guidance, several Indian Wushu athletes have excelled on the international stage, securing medals at prestigious events like the Asian Games and other global competitions. His unparalleled coaching expertise and dedication to his athletes have earned him recognition as one of the best coaches in the world. His legacy continues to inspire and shape the future of Wushu in India.

latestPosts.caption:
Parveen Kumar, a prominent Wushu athlete from India, was honored with the prestigious **Arjuna Award** in 2020. The Arjuna Award is one of India's highest sports honors, awarded to athletes for their outstanding achievements in their respective sports.

Parveen Kumar received the award in recognition of his remarkable contributions to Wushu. He has represented India in various international competitions and has been successful in multiple tournaments, including the **World Wushu Championship** and **Asian Wushu Championship**. His dedication and achievements in the sport have made him one of the leading figures in Indian Wushu.
